…as divers rescue 11 boat mishap victims The Homicide Section of the State Criminal Intelligence and Investigations Department (SCIID), Panti, Yaba, Lagos State, have launched investigation into the death of a 50-year-old man, Mr Sunday Usenbong, who allegedly fell into a melting pot in a factory at Odogunyan area of Ikorodu. Usenbong was said to be operating the company’s machine at Landcraft Industry on November 22, at about 3:33a.m.when he suddenly fell into the melting pot and died. Homicide detectives were drafted to the scene and the remains of the victim had been evacuated and deposited at public mortuary for autopsy, while investigation is still on-going. In another development, 11 passengers among 13 that fell into lagoon after their boat capsized at Itu Agan area of Amuwo Odofin, Lagos, have been rescued. The boat, conveying the victims was said to have collided with Nigeria Port Authority boat, with 13 passengers on board. As at press time, two passengers were still missing. The Lagos State Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), Bala Elkana, while confirming both incidents, explained that after both boats collided, the passenger boat capsized, emptying its passengers into the water. He said: “Immediately, a team of Marine Policemen, fire-fighters, Lagos State Emergency Management Agency (LASEMA) and other responders swiftly moved to the scene and rescued 11 passengers, while a search operation is still on going at the scene for others.” The image maker disclosed that in another incident that occurred at the National Stadium, Surulere on November 17, at about 5:10pm, 26-year-old man, identified as Sodiq Yusuf, drowned while swimming. Elkana noted: “When Police received a distress call that someone drowned, a team quickly moved to the scene. The victim was brought out of the swimming pool and rushed to Randle General Hospital, Surulere, where he later died. His remains were deposited at the Mainland General Hospital morgue, Yaba, for autopsy.”